Q6.1: You have to manually check to see if people add songs to the playlist (at the very least, I can't find a way to be notified when people add songs to the playlist), and it's sort of hard to see if other people are actually listening to the playlist or not. There's not really a history function and no control over other people's actions in the playlist - for example someone can just delete your song and you'd never know who it was, and maybe not even know it was ever in the playlist to begin with.
Q6.2: It would be cool to have a function where I could play songs that were added to the playlist by a specific person/people, or maybe more generally, a function that let me play only songs contributed by other people and no songs I contributed myself. I also think that having a way to opt-in to notifications of when people add songs to the playlist would be cool so I just know when people add new songs (and what they are) instead of not realizing that they did or having to check regularly. It would also be interesting to perhaps have a way for individual collaborators to rate/comment on songs in the playlist, whether they like it or not, and other things.
